00:36:45.648 --> 00:36:48.330
Or is it just like a
temporary flash in the pan?

00:36:48.330 --> 00:36:49.640
DAVID SUMPTER: Yeah.

00:36:49.640 --> 00:36:53.590
I mean, that's the big
question, isn't it?

00:36:53.590 --> 00:36:56.620
I think there is something
to learn in there, because we

00:36:56.620 --> 00:36:59.330
can see there is a statistical
difference between them.

00:36:59.330 --> 00:37:02.440
So and what you see in football
is this constant evolution.

00:37:02.440 --> 00:37:05.330
So the Barcelona
team of 2010-11,

00:37:05.330 --> 00:37:08.000
there were lots of teams
which tried to copy that.

00:37:08.000 --> 00:37:12.190
Like, Swansea tried to do this,
and Arsenal to some degree

00:37:12.190 --> 00:37:13.520
have tried to play like this.

00:37:13.520 --> 00:37:14.970
And now it doesn't work anymore.

00:37:14.970 --> 00:37:18.950
You can't attack through the
D because-- I think really

00:37:18.950 --> 00:37:20.470
Mourinho is credited with this.

00:37:20.470 --> 00:37:23.010
He came up with, well, you just
pack everyone in the middle

00:37:23.010 --> 00:37:26.005
and only Messi is going to
get through that and not

00:37:26.005 --> 00:37:28.130
even Messi is going to get
through it all the time.

00:37:28.130 --> 00:37:30.586
So he came up with a defense
which counteracted that.

00:37:30.586 --> 00:37:31.960
When he played
against Barcelona,

00:37:31.960 --> 00:37:34.684
he let them go out to the
edges as much as they wanted

00:37:34.684 --> 00:37:36.100
because they were
all tiny so they

00:37:36.100 --> 00:37:38.440
couldn't cross in to the
players in the middle.

00:37:38.440 --> 00:37:42.370
So that's one thing where you
see this tactical evolution.

00:37:42.370 --> 00:37:46.265
And Leicester seem to
have evolved a system

00:37:46.265 --> 00:37:48.770
that the others weren't
ready to handle.

00:37:48.770 --> 00:37:52.550
And the problem with
Arsenal is possibly

00:37:52.550 --> 00:37:54.410
they were actually
maximizing something.

00:37:54.410 --> 00:37:57.800
They were maximizing-- we
often call this expected goals.

00:37:57.800 --> 00:37:59.760
They were maximizing
that shots should

00:37:59.760 --> 00:38:02.380
come from a certain area,
and the other teams knew

00:38:02.380 --> 00:38:04.810
that they were
maximizing that and then

00:38:04.810 --> 00:38:05.920
they started blocking it.

00:38:05.920 --> 00:38:07.440
And then Arsenal didn't do well.

00:38:07.440 --> 00:38:09.840
But they had no strategy
for dealing with Leicester.

00:38:09.840 --> 00:38:12.980
So there's this constant
evolution and feedback.

00:38:12.980 --> 00:38:15.950
And, yeah, you will see teams
copying Leicester next season,

00:38:15.950 --> 00:38:18.340
but it's not a guarantee
that it will work.

00:38:18.340 --> 00:38:19.970
Something else might come along.

